body:
Every function and state variable needs a visibility:
- public: callable from anywhere, including other contracts
- external: callable only from outside the contract (slightly cheaper than public for large inputs)
- internal: callable only from this contract and contracts that inherit from it
- private: callable only from this exact contract, not even by children

EXAMPLE:
contract Vault {
    uint256 private secretBalance;

    function _updateBalance(uint256 amt) internal {
        secretBalance = amt;
    }

    function deposit() external payable {
        _updateBalance(secretBalance + msg.value);
    }
}

WHY IT MATTERS: 'private' doesn't mean secret -- all blockchain data is publicly readable regardless of the keyword. Visibility controls who can CALL a function, not who can SEE the data. This trips up almost every beginner at least once.

FURTHER READING:
- Solidity docs, Visibility and Getters: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/contracts.html#visibility-and-getters

