body:
Mappings are key-value stores (like a hash map) that live in storage. Structs let you bundle related data into a custom type. Together they're the backbone of most contract state design.

EXAMPLE:
struct User {
    uint256 balance;
    bool isActive;
}

mapping(address => User) public users;

function register() external {
    users[msg.sender] = User({balance: 0, isActive: true});
}

WHY IT MATTERS: Mappings can't be iterated over directly (there's no 'get all keys' function) -- this is a deliberate gas-safety design. If you need a list of all users, you must maintain a separate array alongside the mapping.

FURTHER READING:
- Solidity docs, Mapping Types: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/types.html#mapping-types
- Solidity docs, Structs: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/types.html#structs

