ERC-20 is the standard interface for fungible tokens. It requires: totalSupply, balanceOf, transfer, approve, allowance, transferFrom, and two events (Transfer, Approval).

EXAMPLE (simplified core):
mapping(address => uint256) public balanceOf;
mapping(address => mapping(address => uint256)) public allowance;

function transfer(address to, uint256 amount) external returns (bool) {
    balanceOf[msg.sender] -= amount;
    balanceOf[to] += amount;
    emit Transfer(msg.sender, to, amount);
    return true;
}

function approve(address spender, uint256 amount) external returns (bool) {
    allowance[msg.sender][spender] = amount;
    emit Approval(msg.sender, spender, amount);
    return true;
}

WHY IT MATTERS: The approve/transferFrom pattern (letting a contract spend your tokens on your behalf) is what powers every DEX swap and DeFi deposit. In production, always use OpenZeppelin's audited ERC20 implementation rather than writing your own.

FURTHER READING:
- EIP-20 spec: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-20
- OpenZeppelin ERC20 docs: https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/erc20

