A multisig (multi-signature) wallet requires M-of-N approvals before executing a transaction -- e.g. 2 of 3 designated owners must sign. Gnosis Safe is the industry standard implementation, securing billions in assets.

Simplified core idea:
mapping(bytes32 => uint256) public confirmations;
uint256 public required = 2;

function confirmTransaction(bytes32 txHash) external onlyOwner {
    confirmations[txHash]++;
    if (confirmations[txHash] >= required) {
        _execute(txHash);
    }
}

WHY IT MATTERS: Multisigs are the standard way serious projects manage treasuries and admin privileges -- no single compromised key can drain funds or make unilateral changes. If you're building anything holding real value, plan for multisig-controlled admin functions from the start.

