Staking contracts let users lock tokens to earn rewards over time. The standard pattern tracks each user's stake, a reward rate, and calculates owed rewards based on elapsed time -- without needing to loop over all users (which would be gas-prohibitive).

Simplified reward-per-token pattern:
mapping(address => uint256) public staked;
mapping(address => uint256) public rewardDebt;
uint256 public rewardPerTokenStored;

function stake(uint256 amount) external {
    _updateReward(msg.sender);
    staked[msg.sender] += amount;
    token.transferFrom(msg.sender, address(this), amount);
}

WHY IT MATTERS: The 'reward per token' accounting pattern (rather than looping through users) is a core DeFi primitive that shows up in staking pools, yield farms, and liquidity mining programs across the ecosystem.

